# IMPL PLAN: Integrate NKRV Bible (Hanja to Hangul)

The goal is to generate a usable Korean Revised Version (NKRV) bible JSON file from source [.bdf](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EB%82%98%EC%9D%98%20%EC%82%AC%EB%9E%91%ED%95%98%EB%8A%94%20%EC%B1%85/public/data/kchNKRV2.bdf) files, ensuring Hanja (Chinese characters) are converted to Hangul for readability, and integrate it into the [BibleService](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EB%82%98%EC%9D%98%20%EC%82%AC%EB%9E%91%ED%95%98%EB%8A%94%20%EC%B1%85/src/services/BibleService.js#70-126).

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Hanja Conversion Strategy**: The source files contain Hanja (e.g., `太初`). I will use the `hanja` npm package to convert these to Hangul (e.g., `태초`). This requires adding a dev dependency to [package.json](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EB%82%98%EC%9D%98%20%EC%82%AC%EB%9E%91%ED%95%98%EB%8A%94%20%EC%B1%85/package.json).

## Proposed Changes

### Scripts
#### [NEW] [scripts/convert_nkrv.cjs](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/나의 사랑하는 책/scripts/convert_nkrv.cjs)
- **Function**:
    - Iterate through [kchNKRV1.bdf](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EB%82%98%EC%9D%98%20%EC%82%AC%EB%9E%91%ED%95%98%EB%8A%94%20%EC%B1%85/public/data/kchNKRV1.bdf) to [kchNKRV7.bdf](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EB%82%98%EC%9D%98%20%EC%82%AC%EB%9E%91%ED%95%98%EB%8A%94%20%EC%B1%85/public/data/kchNKRV7.bdf).
    - Decode content using `EUC-KR`.
    - Convert text using `hanja` library.
    - Parse lines (format: `01창 1:1 Content...`) into JSON structure.
    - Map Korean book abbreviations (e.g., "창") to English keys (e.g., "gn").
    - Save output to `public/data/ko_nkrv.json`.

### Dependencies
- Add [hanja](https://www.npmjs.com/package/hanja) to `devDependencies`.

### Source Code
#### [MODIFY] [src/services/BibleService.js](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/나의 사랑하는 책/src/services/BibleService.js)
- Update [loadBibleData](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EB%82%98%EC%9D%98%20%EC%82%AC%EB%9E%91%ED%95%98%EB%8A%94%20%EC%B1%85/src/services/BibleService.js#86-110) to handle `NKRV` version request by fetching `/data/ko_nkrv.json`.
- Ensure proper fallback and loading states.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Verification
- **Script Execution**: Run `node scripts/convert_nkrv.cjs` and verify it completes without error.
- **File Check**: Verify `public/data/ko_nkrv.json` exists and is approx 4-5MB in size.
- **Content Check**: Read a sample from the generated JSON to ensure `太初` became `태초`.

### Manual Verification
- Start the app.
- Select "NKRV" (or equivalent Korean version) in the Bible reader.
- Verify Genesis 1:1 reads correctly in Korean without Hanja.
